cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image-based virtual try-on systems, which involves computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves geometric matching and learning-based methods, which are related to graphics and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely categories. The paper proposes a new fully-learnable network, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper addresses real-world challenges in virtual try-on, which involves problem-solving and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
